Three-fourths of his vocabulary may be found in Livy, and in the extracts given there are very few words that would strike a Latin scholar as unusual in prose. The chief deviations in Syntax have been indicated by reference to the Grrammar ; and other peculiarities are mentioned in the Notes, which have been taken largely from Prof. Vogel’s school edition (Berlimiffio-Trz).
